<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-06T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-06T15:00:00-05:00" n="572" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d572">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3531/1524: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Armour</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-06T16:00:00-04:00">June 6, 1940—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>93. Department’s telegram no. 81 of May 29, 6 p.m. Please telegraph any
                            reaction so far expressed by Argentine officials to the proposal
                            contained in Department’s 79<note n="29" xml:id="d572fn1">Dated May 27,
                                    <ref target="#pg_484">p. 484</ref>.</note> regarding possible
                            coordination of corn marketing activity.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>